Utterance: Hi again! It's good to see you. How have you been since our last session?
Hi, Ellie! I've been okay, I guess. Some days are better than others.
I understand. Can you tell me more about what has been better or worse?
Well, I had a few good days where I felt more motivated. But then I had a couple of rough days where I felt really low.
That sounds challenging. What do you think triggered those rough days?
I think it was just a mix of stress from work and feeling overwhelmed with everything going on in my life.
That makes sense. Have you been able to use any coping strategies we discussed last time?
A little bit. I've been journaling more, and it does help sometimes.
That's great to hear! What have you been writing about?
Mostly my feelings and some of the things that have been bothering me. It helps to get it out of my head.
Absolutely, expressing your thoughts can be very therapeutic. Have you noticed any patterns in your writing?
Yeah, I noticed that I often write about feeling inadequate or comparing myself to others.
That’s an important insight. Can you tell me more about those feelings of inadequacy?
I guess I just feel like I should be doing more with my life. Sometimes I see friends achieving things, and I feel stuck.
It’s common to feel that way, especially when comparing ourselves to others. How do you usually respond to those feelings?
I tend to withdraw and isolate myself when I feel that way.
That’s understandable. Isolation can feel like a safe option, but it can also make things harder. Have you tried reaching out to anyone during those times?
Not really. I usually just keep it to myself.
Would you be open to trying to reach out to someone next time you feel that way?
I could try that. Maybe talking to someone would help.
That sounds like a positive step. Who do you think you might reach out to?
Probably my aunt. She’s always been supportive.
That’s a great choice! It sounds like you have a strong connection with her.
Yes, I do. She always knows how to make me feel better.
Have you had a chance to talk to her recently?
Not in a while. I’ve been so busy with work and everything.
How about setting a goal to have a chat with her this week?
That would be nice. I’ll try to make time for that.
Wonderful! Let’s also talk about your sleep. Have there been any changes since we last spoke?
Not really. I still struggle with falling asleep and staying asleep.
I see. Have you tried any new techniques to help with your sleep?
I’ve been trying to meditate before bed, but sometimes my mind just races.
Meditation can be tricky, especially if your mind is busy. Would you be interested in exploring some guided meditation resources?
Yes, that could be helpful.
Great! I can share some links with you after our session. Have you noticed any particular thoughts that keep you up at night?
Mostly just worries about work and my future.
That’s understandable. It can be hard not to think about those things. Have you tried writing down your worries before bed?
No, I haven’t thought about that.
It might help to get those thoughts out on paper. You could even write a short list of things you can address tomorrow.
That sounds like a good idea. I’ll give it a try.
Excellent! How have you been feeling about your work situation?
It’s been tough. I feel like I’m not making the impact I want to.
What do you feel is holding you back from making that impact?
I think it’s a mix of my own self-doubt and the limitations of the tutoring job.
That’s understandable. What changes would you like to see in your work?
I’d love to get back into teaching full-time. I miss it.
That’s a great goal! What steps do you think you could take to move closer to that?
I could start looking for teaching positions and maybe take some workshops to improve my skills.
Those sound like actionable steps! Would you like to set a timeline for that?
Yes, I think I could aim to start looking by next month.
That sounds like a solid plan. Let’s check in on that next session.
Sure!
Before we wrap up, is there anything else on your mind that you’d like to discuss?
Not really. I feel like we covered a lot today.
I agree! You’ve made some great insights today. I look forward to hearing about your progress next time.
Thank you, Ellie! I appreciate your help.
You’re welcome! Take care, and I’ll see you soon.
Bye!
